# Stack

Full detail: `Tech_Stack_Decision_Record.md`. Do not add tools without updating that record.

## Required tools

- **.NET 8** — LTS; self-contained Windows publish (`global.json`)
- **C#** — nullable on; `TreatWarningsAsErrors` on all projects
- **xUnit** — sole test framework for Core
- **WebView2** — sole HTML engine for badge print
- **System.Text.Json** — API deserialization
- **JsonSchema.Net** — contract validation against pinned `schemas/`
- **WinForms** — hidden WebView2 host + tray (`NotifyIcon`) in MVP
- **GitHub Actions** — CI (ubuntu Core tests + windows build)

## Do NOT introduce

QuestPDF, PdfSharpCore, iText, or any client-side badge layout library; `ShellExecute` print verb; rendering from `badge_document` JSON; thermal/ZPL SDKs; npm/Node in this repo; WPF **and** WinForms mixed without Tech Stack update.

**PdfiumPrinter** is allowed only as PDF **spooler** after WebView2 renders HTML to PDF — not for layout.

## Hard runtime rules

- Print **only** server `badge_html` — platform `renderBadgeDocument` is the sole layout authority
- Poll interval **1000 ms** — match Node relay; not operator-configurable
- One relay instance per desk secret
- No print dialog during check-in or test print (PRD §8.3)
- Never log relay secret or full setup code
- Operator UI never shows event ID, secret, or full API URL
- Contract changes require parent PRD §26 — bump `schemas/platform-pin.json` when platform schemas change
